  "prompt": "How should I prepare for my CBSE 12th class maths exam?",
  "response": "Preparing for your CBSE 12th class Maths exam requires a strategic and disciplined approach. Here are some effective tips to help you prepare:\n\n### 1. **Understand the Syllabus and Exam Pattern**\n   - Familiarize yourself with the syllabus and the weightage of each chapter.\n   - Understand the exam pattern: 80 marks for theory and 20 marks for internal assessment.\n\n### 2. **Create a Study Schedule**\n   - Plan a realistic timetable, allocating more time to difficult topics.\n   - Cover all chapters, giving priority to high-weightage topics like Calculus, Algebra, and Probability.\n\n### 3. **Master the NCERT Textbook**\n   - Focus on NCERT as it is the primary resource for CBSE exams.\n   - Solve all examples, exercises, and miscellaneous questions thoroughly.\n\n### 4. **Practice Regularly**\n   - Solve previous years\u2019 question papers and sample papers to understand the exam pattern and difficulty level.\n   - Practice numerical problems daily to improve speed and accuracy.\n\n### 5. **Focus on Important Topics**\n   - Calculus: Limits, Continuity, Differentiation\n   - Algebra: Matrices, Determinants, Linear Programming\n   - Probability and Vectors: Understand concepts and practice problems.\n   - Integration: Practice different methods of integration and their applications.\n\n### 6. **Revise Formulas and Concepts**\n   - Make a list of all important formulas, theorems, and concepts.\n   - Revise regularly to ensure you retain information.\n\n### 7. **Work on Weak Areas**\n   - Identify topics you find challenging and spend extra time on them.\n   - Seek help from teachers or classmates if needed.\n\n### 8. **Attempt Mock Tests**\n   - Take full-length mock tests under timed conditions to improve time management and build confidence.\n   - Analyze your performance and work on mistakes.\n\n### 9. **Stay Healthy and Positive**\n   - Take breaks, eat well, and get enough sleep to stay focused.\n   - Avoid stress and maintain a positive attitude.\n\n### 10. **Last-Minute Tips**\n   - Revise key formulas, theorems, and concepts a day before the exam.\n   - Avoid studying new topics at the last minute.\n   - Keep all necessary items (admit card, stationery, calculator, etc.) ready the night before.\n\n### Additional Resources:\n   - Refer to RD Sharma or RS Aggarwal for extra practice.\n   - Use online resources like YouTube channels, apps, and websites for video tutorials and additional practice.\n\nGood luck with your preparation! Stay consistent and confident, and you\u2019ll perform well in your exam.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
